review_blob: A truely outstanding beer.  Often bashed because it is owned by a national brewery.  Hey whats the problem...Good beer for less money!
This a decent dark beer, however for the price there are better ones out there
This stuff is amazing, especially the price.
Good Black and Tan offering from yuengling.  Not as good as Guinness and Bass, but is a good substitute.
A wonderful Ale from Yuengling.  There are no complaints here, it is the best of what can be expected from the style.
Not my favorite from Erie Brewing, but it represents what a good Pilsner should.
Erie Brewings most recognized beer always offers a smooth, sweet taste.  Clearly, a home-town favorite
